./..venv
.env

.venv/

# Byte-compiled / optimized / DLL files
__pycache__/
*.py[cod]
*$py.class

./*.so
# the __pycache__ directory is where Python stores bytecode-compiled versions of modules. The *.py[cod] pattern matches any files with extensions .pyc, .pyo, or .pyd, which are also generated by Python during the compilation process. The *$py.class pattern is used to ignore any files that end with $py.class, which are typically generated by Jython (a Java implementation of Python) when compiling Python code to Java bytecode. The ./*.so pattern is used to ignore any shared object files (dynamic libraries) that may be generated when compiling C extensions for Python.

./..venv/
# the ./.venv/ pattern is used to ignore the virtual environment directory, which is

./...__pycache__/